                            <comment id="15953858" author="dhalperi@google.com" created="Mon, 3 Apr 2017 17:18:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tgroh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tgroh&quot;&gt;tgroh&lt;/a&gt; can you take a look and comment on issue / fix? Maybe starter bug?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15954228" author="tgroh" created="Mon, 3 Apr 2017 22:08:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When the AvroCoder provider is set, the output of the &lt;tt&gt;Values&lt;/tt&gt; transform is set to &lt;tt&gt;AvroCoder&lt;/tt&gt;. When the provider is not set, its output is (correctly) set to &lt;tt&gt;VarLongCoder&lt;/tt&gt;. This means that there&apos;s a bug somewhere in our coder propagation and inference.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15989551" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 28 Apr 2017 22:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user robertwb opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/2771&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/2771&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-1642&quot; title=&quot;Combine transformation evaluation fails on direct runner with Avro as a fallback coder&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-1642&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BEAM-1642&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Try PTransform-based coder inference before using fallback coder.&lt;/p&gt;

